Dear Raceland Family,

I‚Äôm writing to inform our community that a Preschool staff member at Campbell Elementary School has been exposed to a positive COVID-19 case.

Out of an abundance of caution, we have asked all of our Preschool staff to self-quarantine while we await test results for our staff member. All small-group preschool classes will be cancelled until further notice. Virtual instruction for preschool will continue as scheduled next week.

Our paramount concern is the safety and well-being of our students, staff, and community.

If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact me. We will distribute additional information as it becomes available via social media channels. Please continue to wear masks, practice social distancing and remain safe. #ThisIsHome

Sincerely,

Larry Coldiron
Superintendent

post_text:
At the recommendation of Gov. Andy Beshear, and subsequent directive from the Kentucky Department of Education today, Raceland-Worthington Independent Schools will start instruction on-line with virtual learning beginning on Aug. 26th, with in-person instruction suspended until at least Sept 28th, 2020.

After much planning, polling and preparing, our district was set to welcome nearly 70% of our students back to in-person instruction, while developing curriculum to facilitate virtual learning for students at home. While we must alter our plan in the absence of in-person instruction, our teachers, staff and administration remain committed to connecting with Raceland-Worthington students in a meaningful way. The education of each and every student remains our top priority.

We have the greatest staff around who continually rise to the occasion with the creativity, compassion, and determination to serve the children of Raceland-Worthington Independent Schools.

#ThisIsHome

post_text:
We are happy to announce Online Registration for our Annual Update for the 2020-2021 school year.

Submitting this Annual Update virtually for existing Raceland students (as well as incoming Raceland students) is an important step to reduce paperwork and keep our staff safe. A link to Online Registration can be found on our district website. From the website, you'll find a link to Infinite Campus where you'll need a parent-portal login.

This Annual Update and Online Registration allows our district to streamline an enormous amount of paperwork. You'll find the Code of Conduct handbook approval, Technology approval, Media and Field-trip approvals located on Infinite Campus parent-portal.

Please complete the Online Registration for your students and submit the Annual Update at your convenience. Thank you!

https://www.raceland.kyschools.us/Content2/olr

It is with heavy hearts we inform our community former Board-Chairman Mr. Steve Burkhardt passed away.

Steve was a R-W Board of Education member for 28 years. He was a friend, a mentor, and he inspired generations of Raceland students, staff and Administrators. He was a leader and public servant who dedicated his time to make our communities great.

Please join us in praying for his family.

post_text:
The circumstances surrounding year-end events for the Class of 2020 are heartbreaking. It‚Äôs difficult to see our seniors' disappointment. The want to be together during this time and we wish it were possible!

We will never be able to do enough for the Class of 2020, but we felt like we had an ace card to play thanks to our partnership with Ben Spicer and My Town TV HD. Peyton Elizabeth Photography also offered her beautiful photography services to these special Seniors.

Many thanks to Peyton and Ben for helping making this a special occasion and giving them something they can keep for posterity. Please consider helping support MyTownTV by becoming a Supporter. They do so much for our kids. And for your photography needs, please remember Peyton Hale.

To our amazing community: We have watched so many of you shower blessings on this group of Seniors! You‚Äôve been amazing! Please make plans to join us on May 22nd at 7:00 pm as we broadcast virtual graduation and we ask you continue to honor these amazing students with us!

#ThisIsHome

post_text:
Raceland School employees: We understand many of you are trying to obtain masks in accordance with Gov. Beshear‚Äôs recommendation during the ongoing pandemic. We have made arrangements to supply our employees with masks, and they should be in stock at the end of this week. We will distribute to buildings when we receive the shipment from DSI. These will be free to employees.

DSI will have masks available for sale as well. Thanks to them for helping us make these available to our employees.

#ThisIsHome
shared_text:
Distinctive SpecialTees, Inc.
May 2 at 12:21 PM ¬∑

In the coming days and weeks ahead we should have some of these masks available to purchase (there are many variables in the mask purchase, style, and delivery of stock from suppliers). These masks will be Bella Canvas 4.2 oz Ringspun Cotton masks, with Raw Edges. They are Single Layer One Size Fits Most, Ideal for One-Day Use Masks. Logo placement on these masks are in an area to allow unobstructed breathing from any design logo placed on the mask. Our store will remain closed due to Covid19 but you can reach out here with any interest. As many of you know we have not been a frequent Facebook user due to the demands of our business, but in trying times you make adjustments. We are evolving in a new world and will continue to try to provide quality products at an affordable price as we have for the previous 28 years. We thank all of you that have made an impact on our lives in so many ways along this journey and we wish everyone good health as we forge ahead.

Also an additional thank you to Raceland Worthington Schools for their initial purchase of these masks.

The Campbell Elementary playground and the Campbell Pre-School playground are going up! It's an exciting time and we are eager for it to be complete.

When finished, the playground with be a National Demonstration Site complete with pour-in-place rubber around the play structures. This will allow ADA accessibility.

We want to take this opportunity to publicly thank one of our community partners. Bridgeport Equipment & Tool has gone above and beyond to help Raceland-Worthington Schools. If you have lawnmower, equipment or tool needs, stop in and check them out! Let them know how much you appreciate what they do for our school district!

post_text:
Upon the recommendation of Governor Andy Beshear, Raceland-Worthington Schools will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th. The closure will last at least two weeks and will extend to all school related activities.

Raceland-Worthington Schools were previously scheduled to be closed tomorrow, Friday, March 13th. We will observe that closure as well.

The district will continue providing future updates regarding the non-traditional instruction program. We will also provide future updates regarding important non-congregate feeding of students. Stay tuned for additional details, including Chromebook and NTI packet pick-up next week. We greatly appreciate your patience as we work through this extremely fluid situation.

Core Essentials is a national program that is all about character-building and involves focusing on one character trait per month. Each trait fits into the"Big 3," which is 1) Treat others right, 2) Make smart decisions, and 3) Maximize Potential.

At Worthington Elementary School, Mrs. Ison teaches lessons in counseling class throughout the month that reinforces the trait. Each morning, a student reads a fact of the day about that trait on the announcements.

This month's trait is "Creativity: Using your imagination to do something unique." Next month's trait is Forgiveness. #ThisIsHome

post_text:
Raceland-Worthington Board of Education is committed to providing all students with a supportive, safe and positive learning environment. We commend the students who attended the recent board of education meeting on Monday, February 17th to voice their concerns. What we witnessed during that meeting were courageous voices from our students. These students have promoted dialog that will lead to positive growth within Raceland schools. Their voices have set the discourse that will shape the conversation about bullying with all of our young people. This dialog will continue, within our board of education, our administration, to our teachers in classrooms, and to the parents in our community as they gather around the dinner table at home.

We care and will continue our commitment to provide the best environment for the students that choose to attend Raceland Worthington Independent Schools.
